This PR types the `call()` function `data` and `response`:

```ts
// background
import { makeBus } from '../src'

import Tab = chrome.tabs.Tab

const bus = makeBus('content', {
  handlers: {
    tabs: {
      get ({ id }): Promise<Tab> {
        return chrome.tabs.get(id)
      }
    }
  }
})
```
```ts
// some other process

// existing bus
bus.call<Tab, { id: number }>('tabs/get', { id: 1 }).then(tab => {
  if (tab) {
    console.log(tab.url)
  }
})
```

This PR doesn't intend to provide any type safety between the handlers and the call, but allows a user to type the call parameters / return itself.

